      "name": "Hemolysis index validation against FDA GCBP experimental data — 5-point operating map",
      "description": "Validation of CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) against in-vitro measurements across five flow-rate/rotational-speed combinations. Mean relative error of 6.3% with no single point exceeding 12%. Acceptance criterion RH < 1 satisfied at all worst-case operating points. This result was generated under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which was the release candidate immediately preceding the production build. The solver development team confirmed that no turbulence-model coefficients or hemolysis power-law constants were altered between the RC and the final release; the only change logged in the build manifest was a correction to the license-server timeout routine. On this basis the validation result is considered directly transferable to the released solver without re-execution of the full validation campaign.",
